==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mound bird
<hw>mound bird</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any of several large-footed short-winged birds
of Australasia, which build mounds of decaying vegetation to incubate
eggs. Called also <altname>mound builder</altname>, <altname>mound
maker</altname>, <altname>megapode</altname>, <altname>brush
turkey</altname>, and <altname>scrub fowl</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> megapode, mound builder, scrub fowl, brush
turkey.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mount</ent>⟦br⟧
